Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.04,0:00:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll speak more to the people over here\Nthan we did before. I didn't realize you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.27,0:00:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't hear.\NAnybody has a problem, raise your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.68,0:00:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody has a problem.\NThere's a man with a problem. Come up
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.12,0:00:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here where you can speak.\N>> Mhm. Can you hear back there now?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.52,0:00:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Better. Okay. Maybe it's the microphone.\NI should speak more directly into it or
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.16,0:00:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,louder.\N>> What? What are they saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:00:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, we should speak louder into the\Nmegaphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.44,0:01:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, okay.\NWell, today we're going to trace the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.72,0:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of consciousness\Nand its evolution over great eons of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.76,0:01:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,time, you see,\Nand then how it manifests in the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.92,0:01:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom and then how that progresses\Nthrough the homminids and through the um
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.64,0:01:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary tree of man. evolutionary\Ntree of man and how that all comes about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.56,0:01:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and what that signifies for our current\Nreality. How many people are here for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.68,0:01:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the first time?\NOh wow, quite a few. All right. Um and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.84,0:01:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody asked me to speak to tell\Nsomething about myself. you know how you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.72,0:01:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,got to be interested in such a thing and\Nall and got into such kind of research
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.79,0:01:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kind of books I did\Nand so I'll give you a five minute
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.47,0:02:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail scr stretch stretch scratch\Npinch no WHAT
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.64,0:02:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,sketch five minute thumbnail sketch you\Nknow
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.72,0:02:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway we said the circumstances of\None's birth are karmically perfect
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.95,0:02:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we get to see that life moves\Nfrom perfection to perfection. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.84,0:02:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, okay. So, the what the world calls\Nthis lifetime then was in 1927 in the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Midwest.\NMy grandfather was Episcopal minister, I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.08,0:02:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,mean, bishop rather, and uh it was\Nrather
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.64,0:02:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,episcalable, very Episcopal, both high\Nand low at the same time. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,one Sunday low church, next Sunday high\Nchurch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it was a very uh fiscal kind of\Na family. They tend to be reserved, you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.28,0:03:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,know, and they they mind their own\Nbusiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the best thing you can say\Nabout them. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nso anyway, uh nothing there was nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.56,0:03:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,went on nothing went on and there was no\Nconscious awareness of existence until
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,age three.\NAt age three, suddenly out of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.36,0:03:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,nothingness, out of voidness, out of\Nvoidness arose, sudden awareness of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.15,0:03:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\NStunning. Stunning. like coming out of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.64,0:03:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the dark into the dazzling sunlight, a\Nstunning awareness of existence and I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.28,0:03:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,realized there I existed.\NI was not pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.40,0:03:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The preceding state was the void. I\Nnever checked it with the arm. Let's do
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with the arm. The preceding state was\Nthe void. Okay. Out of voidness suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.23,0:04:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,there was consciousness aware of itself\Nas existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.59,0:04:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant there was the awareness of\Nexistence arose simultaneously the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.08,0:04:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of non-existence.\NIt would seem that if one is it could
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.72,0:04:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,have come about then one would not have\Ncome into existence and therefore at age
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,three I was confronted with the duality\Nof existence versus non-existence as the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.24,0:04:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimate reality.\Nwhich doesn't get solved until you get
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.80,0:04:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to calibration level 850.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.04,0:04:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,having nothing else to do and being\Nbored to death with childhood
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.08,0:04:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and other children, I couldn't wait till\Nit was over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.32,0:04:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh so while their children played,\Nit seemed terribly boring and they
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.32,0:04:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,seemed to be very physically aggressive\Nand they were dirty little fingernails.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.36,0:04:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all sticking them in each\Nother's eyes and wrestling and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,disgusting sweaty things like that.\NSo anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I sat in a big chair by myself and read\NPlato and Aristotle and Socrates and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.80,0:05:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Aris plays by Aristophan Aristophanes\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.75,0:05:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it was concerned with the philosophy and\Nexistentialism and God knows what signs
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.96,0:05:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of misspent youth and uh\Nnevertheless life was physically arduous
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.96,0:05:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Midwest,\Nyou know, 20 below zero. I had the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.80,0:05:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,biggest paper route in Wisconsin, 18\Nmiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.08,0:05:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh 18 miles on bicycle every day out\Nin the out in the country. They didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,have electricity on one side of the\Nhighway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.19,0:05:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh, one night below zero, uh, fierce\Nblizzard and it was pitch black and the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.80,0:05:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,papers blew out of my bicycle and blew\Nacross the field
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.16,0:06:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was frozen to death and uh, I\Nstarted to cry because the newspapers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,were flying across the field and I\Nwouldn't be able to deliver them to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.36,0:06:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,customers.\NSo, there were the huge snow banks in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wisconsin. The plows, you know, the\Nplows are as high as this room and the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.12,0:06:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,snow piles up as the winter goes on. uh\N15 ft high. So there was a crusty
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,snowbank and I bashed a hole in the\Nsnowbank and I climbed in out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.00,0:06:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,wind into the snow into a ko cave I made\Njust to get out of the furious wind and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.72,0:06:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nvery shortly an incredible state came
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.19,0:06:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,over the mind stopped thinking\Nthere was an infinite presence of such
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.96,0:06:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite beauty and such infinite are\Nand um
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.28,0:07:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence was not different than that\Nwhich I was. I am
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,before all time, after all time, before\Nall universes, after all universes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.12,0:07:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They which I am existed before all\Nuniverses
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.72,0:07:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and will be after all universes have\Ndisappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.44,0:07:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,True. Exist resist. True.\NThe realization of the infinite self is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.40,0:07:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of existence.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.68,0:07:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometime later, father uh in his 29\Nmodel Ford looking for his lost son in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.44,0:07:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the blizzard. Poor father\Nfinds a snowbank and and I feel this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.31,0:07:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,shaking on my ankle or something. And I\Nrealized the father the father thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.19,0:07:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm dying that I will if I don't\Ncome back in the body if I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.28,0:07:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,reactivate the body, reidentify with the\Nbody, he will grieve and think that I
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,have died. Plus, I saw he would hold\Nhimself responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and spend the rest of his life feeling\Nguilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.56,0:08:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So\NI then resumed the the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.36,0:08:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh\Nthen went on with academic career you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.19,0:08:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,know I had a very good academic career\Nand uh
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.96,0:08:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what I was going to even talk\Nabout.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.88,0:08:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what I was going to talk about.\NSo anyway, unusual spiritual experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.27,0:08:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,began at an early age. Oh, as I say,\Nyes, I was a scupulous episcipellian. I
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.91,0:08:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was an acolyte of the bishop. I was a\Nboy soprano.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.64,0:08:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sang Pontis Angelicus above a huge choir\Nin a cathedral incense full choir, full
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.04,0:09:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,orchestra. Unbelievable.\Nthis voice floated out over the audience
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,like an angelic uh energy was going\Nthrough me you know I was the witness of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.95,0:09:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it so henceforth throughout life I've\Nalways been the witness of the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.12,0:09:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that the world calls me or you you know\Nit's more that one is the witness of all
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,huh\Nbut religiosity was there and with as I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.32,0:09:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned this morning the downside of\NChristianity was still strike strong in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.68,0:09:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the 30s uh sin and guilt was very big\Npenance and want saying the rosary, God
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.36,0:09:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,knows what,\Nbut I was very devoted and scrupulous
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.12,0:09:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and lived in dread and fear of sinning.\NSin was like on your soul and God could
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,see this blotch.\NSo I lived in dread that this black
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.56,0:09:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,blotch would appear on the soul screen\Nand God would see this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.56,0:09:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,blotch there. So anyhow,\None day I was out in the woods by myself
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.48,0:10:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and unasked, not even thinking about the\Nsubject, just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.95,0:10:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,wandering through the beauty of the\Nwoods, all of a sudden came a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.80,0:10:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,revelation. A revelation,\Na revelation is a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.44,0:10:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,an unfolding to your conscious awareness\Nout of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.12,0:10:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,has no nothing preceding it, nothing\Naftering.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.60,0:10:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the realization of the highest.\NThis came as a re revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.44,0:10:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of the totality of the suffering of all\Nof mankind throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.88,0:10:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was overwhelming. And the\Nconfrontation was beyond time, beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.51,0:10:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,space.\NThe totality of the suffering of all
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.83,0:11:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind presented as\Na realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.48,0:11:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In that instant I became an atheist.\NI said any god that could allow what I
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.04,0:11:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,have just realized\NI could not worship. And I became a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.39,0:11:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,devout atheist\Nand I went to Catholic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,University, Jesuit University and got\Nstraight A's in theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.88,0:11:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,His idiots believe this crap,\Nbut I got A's. The ones who believed it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.24,0:11:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,got C's and I didn't believe it got A's.\NThat proves they're idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.51,0:11:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It proves to the existence of of God by\NThomas Aquinus is child's play. You
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.39,0:11:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,could demolish that in about\Na twominute argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.07,0:11:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,First cause\Ndoesn't have to be a first cause. It's a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.48,0:11:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,category of thinking this man. Just jump\Nbeyond that. You realize you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:12:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,require a first cause.\NBesides sort of cause causality is an
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.88,0:12:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion of the Newtonian paradigm.\NSo then I went from atheist I became
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.36,0:12:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,more sophisticated and became an\Nagnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.60,0:12:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Agnostic is an aging atheist.\NYou can't prove God exists. Well, you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,can't prove he doesn't either. So\Natheist is stupid. He thinks that God
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.95,0:12:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't exist and he can prove it. Well,\NI'd like to hear him prove it. No, you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.51,0:12:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,can't prove God doesn't exist because\Nthe intellect which calibrates in the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.63,0:12:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,400s is not the instrument. Theology\Nonly calibrates in the 460s.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.68,0:12:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Love doesn't even start till the 500s.\NAnd realization of the presence of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity as the oneness, the oneness of\Nthe presence of God doesn't go on any
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,600. So here's a intellectualization\Ngoing on at 450 called theology trying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.60,0:13:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to prove the existence of God. It's\Nnonsensical to start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.83,0:13:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an intense uh drive to realize\Nthe absolute truth of everything to that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,there there was an intuitive knowingness\Nthat there was a core of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.39,0:13:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of existence\Nand there was a drivenness to search out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.20,0:13:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to discover the truth. exam having\Nexamined theology, atheism, agnosticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.00,0:13:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,theism, and religion, there wasn't too\Nmuch left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.36,0:13:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The I read Zen and got into meditation\Nand then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.51,0:13:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in some kind of an intense drivenness\Ndrove through meditation to go through
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.51,0:13:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,every single barrier.\NAnd there upon that I descend into the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.88,0:14:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,lower levels of hell.\NDante description of hell is absolutely
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.76,0:14:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,brilliantly accurate.\NAt the highest levels is torture and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,death and destruction.\NAll of which is childless play.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are jacks openers. Beyond that\Ncomes despair and then destin
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.16,0:14:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,destitution and then hopelessness.\NAnd as you descend into the pits of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,hell,\Nthere is actually almost like a sign
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.16,0:14:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there that says, "Abandon all hope ye\Nwho pass this point."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.83,0:14:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you come to hopelessness.\NBut the hopelessness and the despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.39,0:14:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just like the highest levels, you're\Nbeyond time. It goes on for eons. That
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.80,0:14:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,experience in the snowbank went on for\Neons.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.32,0:14:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of the depths of hell\Nbeyond that point now also become
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.07,0:14:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,timeless.\NYou experience
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.24,0:15:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite agony of despair and\Nhopelessness from which there you know
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.04,0:15:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no possible recovery. No\Nrecovery is possible from this level of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.68,0:15:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,hell.\NPlus, it goes on for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.00,0:15:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience what eternity is. And if\Nyou weren't scared crapless before, once
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.12,0:15:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you understand what eternity is,\Nyou turn to cold dread and absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.48,0:15:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,despair.\NIn the depths of hell, the depths of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.95,0:15:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,hell, as I said, are timeless. Go on for\Neons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.19,0:15:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A voice came forth from this\Nconsciousness and said, "If there is a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I ask him for help.\NAfter some period of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like oblivion took over again and\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.07,0:16:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,emerged out of oblivion and all\Neverything had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.00,0:16:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,dramatically that which had been the\Nself no longer existed. There was no
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.92,0:16:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,searcher after truth. There was no\Nperson speaking. The mind was silent.
