Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.44,1:24:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about having an intention, applying\Nemotion to it, and then detaching and
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.48,1:24:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that will draw it to you. So I'm I'm\Nvery confused.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.04,1:24:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> How do you do that?\N>> That's my question.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.88,1:24:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Haven't figured that one out yet.\N>> Yeah, I know. That's a little
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.44,1:25:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,circuitous.\N>> Intentionality then
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.00,1:25:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Ndefinable in terms as high as your level
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.48,1:25:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of conscious and awareness has\Ntraversed at that time. You see in the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.19,1:25:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,name of the highest good. You see to\Nhold that which is beneficial in the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.15,1:25:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,name of the highest good. Most any you\Nknow intentionality you know
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.52,1:25:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,most courses on abundance\Nare presuming first of all that you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.63,1:25:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have it otherwise you wouldn't be\Ndoing it right which means you want more
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.19,1:25:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,than what you got which is already a\Nstatement of lack.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.71,1:25:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you start out from a loser position\Nand the book is all about how to get
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.63,1:25:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,from loser position to winner.\NThe difficulty is the loser position
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.67,1:25:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,takes you securiously back to the loser\Nposition.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.23,1:26:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only with the surrendering of\Nwantingness and being completely content
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.36,1:26:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with whatever is at the moment. As we\Nsaid, everything goes from perfection to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.80,1:26:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection.\NAt this point in life, to not have
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.56,1:26:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anything is perfection.\NI walked out of the house with nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.96,1:26:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and wanted nothing.\NJust when it's time for breakfast,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.71,1:26:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody says, "You want an apple?"\NYou walk out onto the street and you
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.52,1:26:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,think it'd be nice to have a ride and a\Nlimo pulls over and says, "For hire."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.76,1:26:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nthe way is to let go of the question
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.32,1:26:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because the question is self-defeating.\NHow can I acquire abundance is already
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.00,1:26:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is already\Ncancel out any possible answer
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.67,1:27:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to be content with what you have and\Nrealize that it is abundance.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.28,1:27:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have now is abundance. What\Npeople are usually talking about is
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.12,1:27:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,monetary.\NThere is no such thing as shortage of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.40,1:27:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,monetary. There's only spending it\Nfaster than you've got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.44,1:27:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a matter of the speed at which\Nso you're living beyond your means
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.63,1:27:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise you wouldn't have poverty.\NPoverty as a socioeconomic label
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.32,1:27:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is whatever you call it.\NI've lived in poverty a great deal of my
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.40,1:27:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,life and\Nwhat the world would call poverty but as
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.12,1:27:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,far as I was concerned it was all you\Ncould want.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.71,1:27:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nletting go of wantingness itself to let
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.19,1:27:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,go wanting\Nand to just see that you already have
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.96,1:28:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,all that you need. Now\Na deficiency of what you want indicates
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.28,1:28:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're coming from the solar plexus\Nwanting this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.36,1:28:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you want more money? You got\Nenough to eat, place to sleep. So, what
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.00,1:28:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,else do you want?\NAmusement,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.00,1:28:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,better car.\NI drive a Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.56,1:28:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,84.\NThe car is to get me from here to there
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.67,1:28:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and it does so. So why do I need\Nsomething newer and more expensive?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.96,1:28:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So\Nwanting this is giving magical ideas to
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.32,1:29:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to more and then feeling a lack. You\Nknow it's an artificial artificial
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.80,1:29:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,artificiality of mentation.\NIf you go from perfection to perfection,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.96,1:29:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can't possibly be suffering\Nfrom lack. You're only suffering from
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.00,1:29:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,imagination.\NThe other way you can define it is that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.19,1:29:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at every moment you are suffering from\Nlack. There's no moment when you
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.60,1:29:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't have more money, bigger car,\Nbigger property, more children, more
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.48,1:29:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,acreage.\NThere's no moment at which you would
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.36,1:29:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ever have abundance. So if lack is\Npossible then abundance is impossible
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.80,1:29:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because the same kind of mentation would\Napply.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.76,1:29:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it with the bank robber. Um on\NMonday he robs this bank. He got
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.71,1:29:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,$38,000. On Wednesday he robbed this\Nbank, got $62,000. On Friday he robbed
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.32,1:29:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,another bank for $18,000. What did he\Nwhat did he do? spend it all in the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.32,1:30:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,meantime.\NBetween Monday and Tuesday, he spent all
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.56,1:30:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,$50,000 and Wednesday he's broke and\Nneeds to bring bring in another bank.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.04,1:30:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it in the heads of all the giant\Ncorporations whose heads have just
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.32,1:30:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,rolled recently.\NYou know, he he's managed to chisel the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.19,1:30:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,company out of $50 million. Is that\Ngoing to make him happy? If I got 50
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.71,1:30:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,million, wouldn't you retire someplace\Nand take it easy? No. he's going to go
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.00,1:30:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for another 10 million or another 20\Nmillion. So he keeps pushing the
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.92,1:30:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,envelope. So you see the difficulty with\Nthe solar plexus is wantingness cannot
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.04,1:30:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,be satisfied.\NYou cannot satisfy wantingness because
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.28,1:30:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,wantingness is an energy of its own. If\N100,000 doesn't satisfy it, now you want
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.63,1:30:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a half a million. That doesn't satisfy\Nit. Now you want a million. That doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.67,1:30:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfy you not wanting 3 million. So\Ncravingness is an energy of the solar
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.52,1:30:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,plexus and it is not satisfiable.\NHow many bed partners can you have in
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.36,1:31:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,one lifetime?\NHow many kids can you molest? I've
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.48,1:31:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,treated a lot of child molesters.\N158.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.84,1:31:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, judge. How can you be so harsh? You\Nonly got arrested for abusing one boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.60,1:31:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was number 158.\Nthat cravingness is not satisfiable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.76,1:31:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, when you let go of sat of\Ncravingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.19,1:31:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that you have from instant to\Ninstant is complete and total.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.32,1:31:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no instant when one is really\Nactually lacking anything in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.56,1:31:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you die of starvation, that's the\Nway you set it up. And that's your
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.15,1:31:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic responsibility that you set it up\Nthat way.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.52,1:31:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to prove the world is wrong. See, the\Nego to prove it's right would be happy
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.56,1:32:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill you. Oh, it doesn't mind at all.\NIt rather see you dead than admit it's
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.88,1:32:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong. No, it's not possible to suffer\Nfrom lack unless one is coming from a
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.44,1:32:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,solar plexus wantingness.\Nwithout wanting this. Life is complete
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.40,1:32:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and total every second.\NYou think, well, I'm hungry and I don't
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.92,1:32:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,want and I want something to eat now and\NI don't have it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.76,1:32:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not saying that you're lacking\Nanything to eat. It's just that you're
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.60,1:32:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting this to have it now is not\Nsatisfying.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.88,1:32:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, who said you should have it in\Nthe first place?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.80,1:32:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is good enough for you.\NYou can never be rich unless you can
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.96,1:32:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,handle being you can handle poverty. You\Ncan handle poverty then you're always
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.23,1:33:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,rich henceforth\Nfrom poverty 50 bucks is riches.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.15,1:33:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to check manure for\Nbought it for 40 bucks, sold it no
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.84,1:33:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,bought it for 10 bucks, sold it for 40\Nbucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.36,1:33:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Drove from Meguireville to Sedona, paid\N10 bucks there at the dairy farm, sold
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.84,1:33:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it there for 40, 30 bucks. Do that a\Ncouple times a week. What more do you
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.52,1:33:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,need?\NAs free as a bird.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.67,1:33:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So joy comes out of the awareness of the\Nsource of your existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.48,1:33:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of joy is the awareness of\Nyour existence. This instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.67,1:33:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So this instant is complete and total.\NDo I need anything beyond this instant?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.63,1:33:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No. There isn't anything else the next\Ninstant can offer me that isn't already
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.36,1:33:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,present in this instant.\NSo if life stopped just this instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.88,1:33:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,bye.\NIt's already complete.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.19,1:34:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To see all that leaves you free of\Nwantingness
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.48,1:34:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because the wantingness will fixate\Non first one thing and then another. And
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.60,1:34:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,after you've got lots of money, it'll\Nwant youth. And now you're old. You'll
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.60,1:34:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,want beauty and you're ugly.\NYou want a better tennis game and you
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.36,1:34:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,know you're too feeble to hit the wall\Nanymore. So cravingness is never
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.67,1:34:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfied.\NNever satisfied. In fact, every time you
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.76,1:34:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfy it, it gets stronger.\NLook at all the people, Enron and
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.60,1:34:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Worldcom and all those people. They made\Nmoney what in the billions or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.52,1:34:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, isn't 5 billion enough for you\Nwoman or H fella?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.04,1:34:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't 5 billion enough? No. With craving\Nthis, five billion is not enough. 10
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.36,1:34:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,billion is not enough. 100 billion is\Nnot enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.60,1:34:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N>> Your impulse then to have the apple then
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.04,1:35:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is not a state of wantingness. It's a\Nmomentary awareness.
